<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 22 at 7:53PM MDT  by NWS Glasgow</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southwestern
Phillips and northeastern Petroleum Counties through 900 PM MDT...
At 753 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 17
miles southwest of Zortman, moving east at 40 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and half inch hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Fourchette and Fred Robinson Bridge.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.50 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
